    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are staring down a difficult slate today, as several core hitters face elite-tier pitching. The undeniable centerpiece of our lineup is **Jackson Merrill**, whose 75.10 efficiency score stands in a tier of its own. He benefits from a favorable matchup against Feltner (xERA 4.63) and a significant +14% park factor boost; the combination of a high-leverage order spot and the potential for a stolen base against a slow-working starter makes him our must-start anchor. Elsewhere, **Drake Baldwin** (61.45) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (57.07) provide the necessary stability in the middle of the order. While **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** fights against a tough Ritchie assignment, his dynamic platoon edge and favorable spot in the order keep his production expectation well within the strong start category.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today\u2019s card involved keeping **Josh Jung** on the bench with a 41.26 score. While **Josh Jung** represents a viable option, the optimizer favored the specific situational advantages of **Andy Pages** and **Heliot Ramos**, both of whom project to exploit stolen base opportunities against slow-delivery pitchers. The volatility of the day is underscored by the difficult matchups for **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Marcell Ozuna**, all of whom are facing high-end arms like Ryan, Webb, and deGrom. While **Kyle Tucker** maintains a respectable 51.92, we are essentially betting on talent over the environment. We must exercise caution with **Marcell Ozuna**, as his poor BvP history against deGrom (44 PAs) tempers his floor significantly. With **Jordan Westburg** currently sidelined on the IL and both **Gunnar Henderson** and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** off today, we are relying on our depth to carry us through a high-difficulty pitching schedule.",
